<HEAD>Navy Satellite Launched</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VANDENBERG AIR FORCE BASE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Navy satellite
designed to help sailors pinpoint their locations at sea was
launched into orbit, officials said today.
   The 383-pound NOVA 2 navigational satellite was boosted into
outer space at shortly before midnight Wednesday, said base
spokesman Capt. John Sullivan.
   ``We had a successful launch, and everything looks good so
far,'' Sullivan said.
   The launch of the satellite aboard a 73-foot Scout rocket was
the first space launching from the Air Force base since April 26.
