<HEAD>Lance Says Party Unity Required For Democrats To Win White House</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MARIETTA, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bert Lance, an adviser to presidential
candidate Jesse Jackson, says party unity will determine whether
the Democrats recapture the White House in November.
   The former budget director under President Carter told an
Atlanta audience Wednesday that the unity depends on Jackson acting
responsibly at the Democratic National Convention in Atlanta July
18-21.
   ``Let's face it,'' Lance said. ``Jesse Jackson's future is with
the Democrats. It's not with the Republicans and it's not as a
half-warm participant. It's in full participation.
   ``There's no reason to think it's not going to be that way,''
Lance said. ``He's going to campaign for the ticket. He's going to
be responsible, he's going to be substantive.''
