<1ST_LINE>r a PM-TNTProgramming     06-16 0193</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-TNT Programming,0199</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Turner Network Television Announces Programming Lineup</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Turner Network Television and ``Gone With The
Wind'' will make their cable television debut together this fall.
   Ted Turner said his newest cable network will debut on cable
systems Oct. 3 with the film classic about the Old South.
   More than half of the network's 24-hour programming will be
drawn from the 3,301 MGM, RKO and pre-1950s Warner Bros. films
owned by Turner Entertainment Co., Turner announced Wednesday.
   The network will also offer original programming, which it
eventually will broadcast 200 to 250 nights a year, according to
Alex Swan, spokesman for Turner Broadcasting System.
   Jim Henson, who created ``The Muppet Show'' and ``Fraggle
Rock,'' will develop new programming for TNT, Turner said.
``Fraggle Rock'' currently is available only to subscribers of the
Home Box Office premium cable channel.
   TNT is already signed for cable systems serving more than 7
million subscribers around the United States, Swan said. That
compares to 44 million households for the 10-year-old WTBS
SuperStation, 46 million households for 8-year-old Cable News
Network and 31.5 million households for 6-year-old CNN Headline
News, all Turner broadcasting operations.
</TEXT>
