<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Greece-Tomato,0161</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Who Threw Tomato at Ozal's Car Sent To Jail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATHENS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A court on Thursday sentenced a Greek
chemist to four months in jail for throwing a tomato at Turkish
Premier Turgut Ozal's car.
   The incident occurred Wednesday on the last day of Ozal's
official visit to Greece, the first by a Turkish premier in 36
years.
   ``I did it because I felt a kind of sacred anger at the
provocation of Ozal's presence in Greece. I've never done such a
thing before,'' Theodoros Binichakis, 42, told the three-member
court before he was sentenced.
   The tomato splattered across the windshield of Ozal's limousine
as it took him back to his hotel after a call on President Christos
Sartzetakis.
   Binichakis was arrested by police on a charge of ``unprovoked
insult.''
   Ozal and Greek Premier Andreas Papandreou said Ozal's visit was
designed to improve relations between the traditionally hostile
NATO allies.
</TEXT>
