<HEAD>Soviet Leader To Visit Poland Next Month</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WARSAW, Poland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Soviet leader Mikhail S. Gorbachev will
visit Poland sometime between July 10-20, the two governments
announced Thursday.
   Gorbachev was invited by Wojciech Jaruzelski, leader of the
Polish United Workers (communist) Party, according to statements by
the Polish state-run PAP news agency and the Soviet news agency
Tass.
   Polish officials have said Gorbachev will visit several cities
and attend a meeting of Warsaw Pact leaders in Warsaw.
   There was no mention of a Warsaw Pact meeting in Thursday's
official announcements. Besides the Soviet Union and Poland, the
pact includes East Germany, Czechoslovakia, Hungary, Romania and
Bulgaria.
   Gorbachev has visited Poland twice before, for a Warsaw Pact
summit in 1985 and for Poland's Communist Party Congress in 1986.
