<HEAD>Bus Wrecks, 16 Burned to Death</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: LEADS throughout to UPDATE with 16 killed, police holding
driver. No pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus blew a tire, hit a wall and burst
into flames today, burning 16 people to death in the southern state
of Andhra Pradesh, the Press Trust of India reported.
   Among the victims were seven children.
   The news agency said the bus, carrying 38 people, wrecked on the
outskirts of the state capital at Hyderabad. It said two people
were being treated for serious burn injuries at a local hospital
and 10 others escaped with minor injuries.
   The driver and the cleaner of the bus, who survived the
accident, have surrendered to the police, PTI said.
   Officials earlier had reported a death toll of 27 but later
corrected it to 16.
