<HEAD>Dutch Students Scuffle With Police Over Cuts In Aid</HEAD>
<DATELINE>THE HAGUE, Netherlands (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hundreds of Dutch students hurled
bricks at Parliament and scuffled with police Thursday during a
protest against a government plan to cut their education grants,
police said.
   Three people were arrested and one window in Parliament was
smashed before riot police dispersed more than 1,000 demonstrators,
said police spokesman Guus Auerbach. He denied a news report that
police had charged the protesers.
   It was the latest in a series of demonstrations against plans by
Eduction Minister Wim Deetman to cut government study grants and
force students to borrow from commercial banks to help finance
their education.
