<HEAD>One Killed And 18 Hurt In Interstate Pileup</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PASCAGOULA, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Five big trucks and four other vehicles
piled up in a series of accidents on smoke-shrouded Interstate 10
on Thursday, killing one driver and injuring 18 people, authorities
said.
   The Highway Patrol said the wreckage blocked the freeway for
eight hours.
   The accidents began around 1:45 a.m. after dense smoke from a
woods fire reduced visibility on the highway north of Pascagoula.
Jackson County forester Andy Redwood said the fire, which charred
about 150 acres of woods about 100 yards north of the interstate,
had been brought under control Wednesday night.
   Besides five 18-wheel tractor-trailer rigs, the wreck involved
two cars, a pickup and a van, said Highway Patrol Capt. Richard
Smith.
   Eight people were admitted at Singing River Hospital at
Pascagoula in stable condition. Seven people were treated and
released. At Ocean Springs Hospital, two people were in
satisfactory condition and a third was treated and released.
   The dead person's identity was not immediately released.
