<1ST_LINE>r a AM-People-Asner     06-16 0258</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Asner,0265</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Attorney: Asner To Pay Child Support</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actor Ed Asner will pay more than $2,100
monthly to the mother of a 10-month-old child he fathered out of
wedlock, a lawyer said Thursday.
   Under the agreement, Asner must pay $2,000 for expenses and $100
for medical insurance each month to support Charles Edward
Vogelman, said attorney Ronald Supancic, who represents the former
husband of the child's mother.
   The actor, who admitted paternity, must also pay the mortgage on
a $300,000 condominium where the child lives with his mother Carol
Jean Vogelman, Supancic said.
   The agreement ends seven months of medical tests and testimony.
Asner, star of television's ``Bronx Zoo'' and the old ``Mary Tyler
Moore Show'' and ``Lou Grant,'' eventually conceded the child was
his.
   The actor became involved in the court action when Ms.
Vogelman's ex-husband, David Stone, alleged his $3,000-a-month
alimony payment was being used to support a child that wasn't his.
   Under the court-supervised agreement, Stone must pay $2,000
monthly to Ms. Vogelman for the next three months, $1,500 monthly
for the following 10 months and $1,000 monthly thereafter.
   ``We thought it was a little out of balance that David Stone was
paying such a high monthly sum when a man of Mr. Asner's stature
had become involved with Ms. Vogelman and they had conceived a
child together,'' Supancic said.
   Asner attorney Michael Schiff said only that Asner and Ms.
Vogelman had reached an oral agreement that was being put into
writing. He didn't dispute the figures detailed by Supancic.
</TEXT>
