<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Italy-Riot     06-16 0178</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Italy-Riot,0184</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Workers Storm Naples City Hall After Hearing Factory Closed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NAPLES, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dozens of furious steelworkers attacked
government offices in Naples after learning that part of their
factory would be closed, officials said Thursday.
   Five traffic police and a doorman were injured when they tried
to block the workers.
   Hundreds of laborers gathered Wednesday in front of the
state-owned Italsider steel mill in Bagnoli, a suburb of Naples, to
protest plans announced a day earlier to close part of the plant.
   After the rally, at least 200 steelworkers went to Naples. They
burst into the offices of the Campania regional government,
smashing desks and chairs and hurling furniture and plants through
the windows, news reports said.
   Workers then proceeded to City Hall where they wrecked furniture
and knocked paintings off the walls.
   Police arrested 30 people and charged them with causing damage.
Others involved in the riot were being sought.
   The government said Tuesday it will cut 25,000 jobs from its
money-losing steel industry under a restructuring plan. The
Italsider plant employs 4,000 people.
</TEXT>
