<1ST_LINE>s a BC-AIDS-Curriculum Adv19   06-16 0375</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-AIDS-Curriculum, Adv 19,0384</2ND_LINE>
<NOTE>$Adv19</NOTE>
<NOTE>For Release Sunday, June 19, and Thereafter</NOTE>
<HEAD>Excerpts From Educator's AIDS Discussion</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-AIDS-Empty Chairs</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are excerpts from ``From Fr-AIDS to Faith: Let Us Talk
About AIDS.'' Religious education director Mary Ann Clemens of
Northbrook, Ill., designed the curriculum to help Roman Catholic
parents explain to children in grades 1-8 the basics of AIDS,
sexuality, and what the Bible says about how AIDS victims should be
treated.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>Grades 1-3:</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   ``A long time ago, Jesus Christ lived in a town with persons who
had questions. In his time there was much sickness and people were
afraid. They did not have AIDS: they had leprosy and other terrible
diseases. Jesus tells us a story in Luke that helps us know how to
treat persons who are sick, especially persons with AIDS ...
   ``God gives us our bodies and we are special. We are to help God
take care of our bodies. God loves ALL of us ...''
</TEXT>
<HEAD>Grades 4-6:</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   ``Bobby ... is upset because he does not understand about Uncle
Ned's illness. Uncle Ned has AIDS ...
   ``How did Uncle Ned Get AIDS? ... One way a person gets AIDS is
by using a needle to stick into their body that has blood in it
from a person with AIDS. Drug users get AIDS this way most of the
time. Another way is by sharing your body fluids with a person with
AIDS in sexual contact ...
   ``Mother says that Ned knows how he caught the virus. Perhaps
someday he will tell you about it ...''
</TEXT>
<HEAD>Grades 7-8:</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   ``Some persons get AIDS from allowing an infected person's body
fluids to enter their body. They get AIDS from sexual contact, for
example, or from French kissing when there is a cut in the mouth ...
   ``You prevent the spread of AIDS by not using drugs. Sexual
intercourse is for married persons, and by not having sex until you
are married you will be sure not to get AIDS. Some persons now are
saying that by using a condom, sex outside of marriage is safe. We
choose not to have sex outside of marriage for other reasons than
safety or health ...''
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Adv for Sunday, June 19</NOTE>
